'''Gérard Dagon''' (4 April 1936, Strasbourg - 22 May 2011, [[Gandrange]])<ref>{{cite web |title=Décès du pasteur Gérard Dagon, l'un des fondateurs de Vigi-Sectes |url=http://topchretien.jesus.net/topinfo/view/89596/deces-du-pasteur-gerard-dagon-lun-des-fondateurs-de-vigisectes.html |publisher=Top Chretien |first=Paul |last=Ohlott |language=French |date=25 May 2011 |accessdate=3 July 2011}}</ref> was a French evangelical [[Protestant]] [[pastor]], teacher, author, publisher and long-time [[Christian countercult movement|Christian counter cultist]]. He was [[Master of Divinity]] at the faculty of Protestant theology in Strasbourg.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Les sectes expliquées en public |url=http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2006/03/06/66828-Les-sectes-expliquees-en-public.html |journal=[[La Dépêche du Midi]] |publisher=La Dépêche Group |place=Toulouse |date=6 March 2006 |language=French |accessdate=3 July 2011}}</ref>

He became pastor of the [[Protestant Reformed Church of Alsace and Lorraine]] (EPRAL) in 1959, then directed the Union of Evangelical Churches Chrischona (Union des Églises évangéliques Chrischona).<ref name="Lacroix">{{cite journal |title=Sectes |url=http://www.la-croix.com/Archives/1998-04-16/Sectes-_NP_-1998-04-16-456639 |journal=[[La Croix]] |first=Benoît |last=Hervieu-Léger |publisher=Bayard Press |place=Paris |date=16 April 1998 |language=French |accessdate=3 July 2011}}</ref> He also participated in the creation of the Evangelical Federation of France ([[:fr:Fédération évangélique de France|Fédération évangélique de France]]) which he directed for a long time.<ref>{{cite book |title=Ces protestants que l'on dit adventistes |first1=Fabrice |last1=Desplan |first2=Régis |last2=Dericquebourg |authorlink2=Régis Dericquebourg |publisher=L'Harmattan |place=Paris |year=2008 |page=25 |language=French |isbn=978-2296068384}}</ref> He founded, alongside others such as Swiss pastor and former member of the [[ADFI]] Paul Ranc, the association Vigi-sectes in 1998 who fights against cults from an evangelical perspective.<ref name="Lacroix"/> He published books about Protestant movements, about Christian-oriented groups he considered [[cult]]s because of their supposed biblical errors,<ref>{{cite book |title=Les sectes en question: Se questionner et questionner |first1=Noël M. |last1=Rath |first2=Marcel |last2=Gilbert |publisher=L'Harmattan |year=2005 |page=55 |language=French |isbn=2-7475-8996-X}}</ref> and an extensive encyclopedia on Christianity. He listed 150 people who have claimed to be the [[Messiah]] from the first century.<ref>{{cite web |first=Paul |last=Ohlott |title=Les prétendants au Trône céleste ! |url=http://www.topchretien.com/topinfo/view/16413/dossier-inedit-les-pretendants-au-trone-celeste.html |work= |publisher=Top Chrétien |language=French |date=20 August 2007 |accessdate=3 July 2011}}</ref>

[[Sébastien Fath]] considered Dagon a "key figure of French evangelical Protestantism since the 1970s,<ref>{{cite book |title=Du ghetto au réseau: le protestantisme évangélique en France (1800–2005) |first=Sébastien |last=Fath |authorlink=Sébastien Fath |publisher=Labor et Fides |place=Genève |language=French |page=194 |isbn=2-8309-1139-3}}</ref> and [[Émile Poulat]] qualified him a "pioneer" in the religious issues.<ref>{{cite book |title=Notre laïcité publique: "La France est une République laïque" (Constitutions de 1946 et 1958) |first=Émile |last=Poulat |authorlink=Émile Poulat |publisher=Berg International |year=2003 |page=259 |language=French |isbn=2-911289-65-X}}</ref> Although his works are often used by sociologists,<ref>{{cite book |title=Les évangéliques dans la France du XXIe siècle |first=Franck |last=Poiraud |publisher=Aparis editions |page=13 |language=French |isbn=978-2-3560-7032-6}}</ref> he also received some criticisms. For example, Secretary of the French episcopate for the study of cults and new religious movements [[Jean Vernette]] said that Dagon used his anti-cult fight to attract new followers to his church.<ref name="Lacroix"/>

