'''Javier Naranjo Villegas''' (21 January 1919 – 7 March 2014) was a [[Colombia]]n [[Prelate]] of [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Villegas was born in [[Abejorral| Abejorral, Colombia]] and was ordained a priest on March 15, 1942. Villegas was appointed bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Santa Marta|Diocese of Santa Marta]] on June 2, 1971 and consecrated on June 29, 1971. Villegas remained at the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Santa Marta|Diocese of Santa Marta]] until his resignation on July 24, 1980.
